# Enrich OS — environment variables
#
# AUDIT NOTE (see PR/commit for context): as of this audit, the codebase has
# ZERO `process.env` reads anywhere. There is no .env file, no Supabase SDK
# dependency, and no environment-driven configuration at all. This file is
# intentionally empty of real entries below — it exists so `cp .env.example
# .env.local` is a safe no-op today, and so the categories are pre-built for
# whenever persistence/config actually moves to environment variables.
#
# All current configuration lives in version-controlled JSON instead:
# config/column-aliases.json, config/confidence-weights.json,
# config/descriptor-list.json, config/pipeline-version.json.
#
# The SQLite database path is HARDCODED in server/db/client.ts
# (`<cwd>/data/enrich-os.db`) — not environment-driven. This will not work
# on Vercel (serverless functions have a read-only filesystem outside
# /tmp, and /tmp does not persist across invocations). Resolving that is a
# prerequisite for deploying to Vercel, independent of anything below.

# --- Required for local development -----------------------------------
# (none — `pnpm install && pnpm dev` works with no .env file at all)

# --- Required for production (Vercel) -----------------------------------
# (none currently defined — and per the note above, the app cannot persist
# data correctly on Vercel until the SQLite-file approach is replaced with
# a networked database or a Vercel-compatible storage layer)

# --- Supabase-related -----------------------------------------------------
# (none — this project has no Supabase integration: no @supabase/* package,
# no SUPABASE_URL/SUPABASE_ANON_KEY/SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY reads anywhere.
# If a Supabase migration is planned, these would need to be introduced
# together with the actual client code that reads them — see "Not yet
# implemented" below.)

# --- Optional ---------------------------------------------------------------
# (none)
